						<summary>

						<p>On a slab fixed into a diapidated wall in the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Bhillama 1184 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged and incomplete record refers to the rule of Yādava king Bhillamadēva. It mentions <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna</hi> Gaṇḍarayya and Vachōrāśī.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Bhillamadēva year 6, [Śaka 1106] Krōdhi, Ā(śvīna), Thursday, <hi rend="italic">vishu saṁkramaṇa.</hi> Probably it corresponds to 1184 A.D., September 27, Thursday [<hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> ba. 6]. There was <hi rend="italic">tulāsaṁkramaṇa</hi> on that day.</p>						

						</summary>
